<h2> Session #1: </h2>
<p> This session was originaly a somewhat open-ended one-shot I had made. The players meet at Greenhill (Πρασινόλοφος) a small village, having both read an "adventurers needed" ad (Θα μου πείτε... τι πιό σύνηθες, να συμβεί...). They are tasked with finding little Timmy, a young boy from the village, who apparently went missing near an old well in the forest. </p>
<p>Upon arriving at said well, the players discover that there is a system of tunnels and caves connected to it, where a wizard has made his laboratory. It appeared that he was trying to raise a dragon by feeding it people from the sorrounding area. After discovering a secret passageway the players head to the dragon's lair, where -thankfully for them- the otherwise powerful dragon youngling was really struggling to roll a good die. After beating the dragon within an inch of its life, the players rescue little Timmy, manage to run away from some slimes and a gelatinous cube and discover that the tunnel systen of the well intersects with some goblin mines. The players decide to talk with the goblins instead of fighting them, and since the Dungeon Master had planned no further the session ends.</p>
